  "prompt": "When a parking sign says 2-hour parking from 8 to 5 on Monday-Friday, what does it mean for the remainder of the time?",
  "response": "When a parking sign indicates \"2-hour parking from 8 to 5 on Monday-Friday,\" it means that during those hours and days, you are permitted to park for up to 2 hours at a time. Outside of those specified hours (before 8 AM and after 5 PM on Monday through Friday, and anytime on weekends), parking is typically unrestricted unless there are other signs or regulations in place. This means you can generally park for extended periods without adhering to the 2-hour limit when the 2-hour restriction is not in effect.",
